en: Place a wedge in the highlighted space.\n\nYou can change a component's rotation by hovering over different adjacent surfaces in the vehicle.
local: 在突出显示的空间中放置一个斜面。\n\n您可以通过将鼠标悬停在载具中不同的相邻表面上来更改组件的旋转

en: Place the next five wedges.\n\nMultiple wedges can be placed at once by dragging.
local: 放置下五个楔子。\n\n可以通过拖动一次放置多个楔子

en:
You can also use the following keys to rotate and flip the component.

[j] rotates on the x axis
[k] rotates on the y axis
[l] rotates on the z axis

[u] flips on the x axis
[i] flips on the y axis
[o] flips on the z axis

[p] toggles the rotation display
local:
也可以使用下列键旋转和翻转组件。

[j]在x轴上旋转
[k]在y轴上旋转
[l]在z轴上旋转

[u]在x轴上翻转
[i]在y轴上翻转
[o]在z轴上翻转

[p]切换旋转显示

en: Click on the pyramid block in the component list to start building with it.
local: 单击组件列表中的棱锥图块开始构建

en:
First, connect the button in front of seat to the engine's 'on/off' node.

This will allow you to switch the engine on by pressing the button.

Click on one of the flashing logic nodes to select it and then drag and release while hovering over the node you want to connect it to.
local:
首先，将座椅前面的按钮连接收到引擎的“开/关”节点。

这将允许您通过按按钮打开引擎。

单击其中一个闪烁的逻辑节点将其选中，然后在悬停在要连接的节点上时将其拖动并释放

en:
Next, connect the 'Axis 2 [$[action_up]]/[$[action_down]]' node from the seat to the engine's 'throttle in' node.

This will allow you to apply throttle power to the engine by pressing [$[action_up]] and [$[action_down]].

Click on one of the flashing logic nodes to select it and then drag and release while hovering over the node you want to connect it to.
local:
接下来，将“轴2[$[action_up]/[$[action_down]]节点从座椅连接收到发动机的“throttle in”节点。

这将允许您通过按[$[action_up]]和[$[action_down]]向发动机应用油门功率。

单击其中一个闪烁的逻辑节点将其选中，然后在悬停在要连接的节点上时将其拖放去吧

en: Next, connect the 'Axis 1 [$[action_left]]/[$[action_right]]' node from the seat to one rudder's 'rotation input' node.\n\nThis will allow you to apply a turning force by pressing [$[action_left]] or [$[action_right]].
local: 接下来，将座椅上的“轴1[$[action_left]/[$[action_right]]'节点连接收到一个方向舵的“旋转输入”节点。\n\n这将允许您通过按[$[action_left]]或[$[action_right]]来应用旋转力

en: Next, connect the 'Axis 1 [$[action_left]]/[$[action_right]]' node from the seat to the the 'rotation input' node in the second rudder.\n\nThis will allow you to apply a turning force by pressing [$[action_left]] or [$[action_right]].
local: 接下来，将座椅上的“轴1[$[action_left]/[$[action_right]]'节点连接收到第二个方向舵上的“旋转输入”节点。\n\n这将允许您通过按[$[action_left]]或[$[action_right]]应用旋转力

en: Finally, connect the power between the engine and propeller.\n\nThis will pass the power created by the engine through to the propeller and allow you to move the boat forward and back with the throttle.
local: 最后，连接发动机和螺旋桨之间的电源。\n\n这将把发动机产生的电源传递到螺旋桨上，并允许您使用油门前后移动船

local: 单击“+”按钮创建一个新的保存文件

en:
Your addon was successfully uploaded to the Steam workshop.

 We recommend heading to your addon's workshop page to add more information about the content you've included.

 Any vehicles used in your addon have been included as part of the upload. Players will not need to separately subscribe to any of these vehicles.

en: You can customise outfits and whether this character is a survivor or NPC in the properties window. Survivors will follow you and can be picked up, but NPCs can not be interacted with.

en: Objects can be picked up, thrown and moved around by the player. They can be used for delivery missions or just as decoration. You can customise the object type in the properties window.
local: 玩家可以捡起、投掷和移动物体。它们可以用于运输任务或仅仅作为装饰。可以在“属性”窗口中自定义对象类型

en: Zones can be used to set up advanced mission behaviour at specific world locations with addon Lua. These zones can be accessed globally by any addon script with functions getZones() and isInZone().
local: 可以在世界中设置一个带有lua插件的区域，来实现更高级的任务功能。创建出的区域可以被任何插件全局访问，访问函数为getZones()以及isInZone()

en: Zones are used to specify a location, these zones are local to a addon and can be accessed like any other local component through getLocationObjectData(). Mission Zones are generally more appropriate for constructing procedural style missions.
local: 区域用于指定一个位置，这些区域是playlist的地点，可以像其他本地组件一样通过getLocationObjectData()来访问。任务区一般更适合构建流程式的任务

en: You can set a vehicle to be static in the properties window. Static vehicles are fixed in place, making them useful for adding buildings or cranes to missions.
local: 可以在“属性”窗口中将载具设置为静态。静态载具被固定在一个位置，这使得它们有助于在任务中增加建筑或机械臂

en: Vehicle buttons allow your mission to interact with a named button on a vehicle. You must parent the button to a vehicle, and set the 'button display name' in the properties window to be the name of a button on the parent vehicle.
local: 载具按钮允许您的任务与载具上的指定按钮交互。必须将按钮设置为载具的父级，并将“属性”窗口中的“按钮显示名称”设置为父级载具上按钮的名称

en: Flares emit a plume of coloured smoke that can be used to get the player's attention in an emergency situation. The colour of the flare can be customised in the properties window.
local: 照明弹会释放出一股彩色烟雾，在紧急情况下可以用来引起玩家的注意。可以在“属性”窗口中自定义照明弹的颜色

en: Fires can be extinguished using water cannons and will spread to other nearby fires. The size of the fire and whether or not it is initially lit can be customised in the properties window.
local: 火焰可以用高压水枪扑灭，并在周围蔓延形成火灾。火焰的大小以及它最初是否被点燃可以在属性窗口中定制

en: Loot boxes allow you to hide additional rewards in your missions. Each one will give the player a random reward with a value between $6000 and $10000.
local: 战利品箱允许你在任务中隐藏额外的奖励。每位玩家将随机获得一份价值在6000到10000美元之间的奖励

en: The animal type can be customised in the properties window. If the 'Sharks' difficulty option is enabled, sharks will stalk and attack characters in the water.

en: Lua scripting gives you the tools to create advanced logic components using the Lua scripting language. Stormworks provides a number of functions to allow your script to interface with your vehicle's logic system, as well as drawing to in-game monitors.\n\nThis guide outlines the functions that are available for use in your scripts but it is not a comprehensive tutorial on using the Lua language.
local:
Lua脚本提供了使用Lua脚本语言创建高级逻辑组件的工具。Stormworks提供了许多功能，允许脚本与载具的逻辑系统进行交互，并绘制到游戏中的屏幕中。

本指南概述了可在脚本中使用的功能，但它不是使用Lua语言的综合系统性教程。

显示器中的绘图均以左上角为坐标原点，向右为X轴正方向，向下为Y轴正方向。文字的坐标为其左上角像素点的坐标值。

游戏中一个单位长度为32个像素，即:

屏幕1x1=32x32像素；

屏幕2x2=64x64像素；

屏幕5x3=160x96像素；

屏幕9x5=288x160像素；

HUD(小)=32x32像素；

HUD(大)=96x96像素

en:
This scripting API is very powerful and as such there are some important reminders to take note of:

- Your script has a max execution time of 1000 milliseconds, however it is still possible to create scripts that significantly slow down the game. It is your responsibility to ensure your script runs efficiently.

- Random number functions are provided by the Lua math library. Use of randomness in your scripts is likely to cause desync in multiplayer, so use these functions at your own risk.

- When your vehicle despawns and respawns, your script will be executed 'fresh' and any state stored within the script will be lost. We recommend keeping your script as stateless as possible, and making use of existing logic components (e.g. memory register) to store values that you wish to persist.

- Your scripts run as a 'black box' with only the logic inputs/outputs being synced in multiplayer. Keep in mind that complex logic in your script may behave differently for different players in a multiplayer session.

- A number of safeguards are in place to sandbox your script, however it is still possible to write scripts that will potentially crash your game. If you crash your game with a script, it's likely that you're doing something (very) wrong. This is your own responsibility. If you suspect you have encountered a legitimate bug, please report it on the Stormworks issue tracker (accessible from the pause-menu).

- Malicious and harmful scripts will not be tolerated on the Stormworks Steam Workshop.

Finally, enjoy the almost limitless possibilities that these scripts provide. This short wiki aims to give a good overview of how scripting in Stormworks works, however if you have any questions that are not covered here, please feel free to join us on Discord (accessible from the pause-menu)!
local:
这个脚本API非常强大，因此有一些重要的提示需要注意:

-您的脚本的最大执行时间为1000毫秒，但是仍然可以创建显著减慢游戏速度的脚本。确保脚本有效运行是您的责任。

-Lua数学库提供随机数函数。在脚本中使用随机性可能会在多人游戏中导致desync，因此使用这些功能的风险由您自己承担。

-当您的载具报废和重生时，您的脚本将被“刷新”执行，脚本中存储的任何状态都将丢失。我们建议尽可能使脚本保持无状态，并使用现有的逻辑组件(例如内存寄存器)来存储希望保持的值。

-脚本作为“黑盒”运行，只有逻辑输入/输出在多人游戏中同步。请记住，脚本中的复杂逻辑对于多人会话中的不同玩家可能会有不同的行为。

-有许多保护措施可以对脚本进行沙箱处理，但是仍然可以编写可能会导致游戏崩溃的脚本。如果你用脚本把游戏搞崩溃了，你(很)可能写错了什么。这是你自己的责任。如果怀疑遇到了游戏本身的错误，请在Stormworks问题跟踪程序(可从“暂停”菜单访问)上报告。

-Stormworks Steam创意工坊不允许恶意和有害的脚本。

最后，享受这些脚本提供的几乎无限的可能性。这个简短的wiki旨在很好地概述Stormworks中的脚本是如何工作的，但是如果您有任何此处未涉及的问题，请随时加入我们的Discord(可从暂停菜单访问)！

5: input2X

2: isInput2Pressed

en: It outputs stabilised values that can be sent to rotors and engines to make them much easier to control. An on/off input allows you to activate and deactivate the internal auto-hover circuit. When auto-hover is enabled, the gyroscope will attempt to keep your helicopter steady.
local: 它输出稳定值，可以发送到螺旋桨和发动机，使它们更容易控制。开/关输入允许您激活和停用内部自动悬停电路。启用自动悬停后，陀螺仪将尝试保持直升机稳定

en: The gyroscope takes 4 standard value signals representing the desired yaw, pitch, roll and vertical motion of a helicopter.
local: 陀螺仪接收4个标准值信号，表示直升机所需的偏航(Yaw)、俯仰(Pitch)、滚转(Roll)和垂直运动

en: Accepts a standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired roll speed.
local: 接受一个介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示所需的滚转(Roll)速度

en: Outputs a standard value between -1 and 1 representing a stabilised roll speed.
local: 输出一个介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示稳定的滚转(Roll)速度

en: Accepts a standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch speed.
local: 接受一个介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示所需的俯仰(Pitch)速度

en: Outputs a standard value between -1 and 1 representing a stabilised pitch speed.
local: 输出一个介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示稳定的俯仰(Pitch)速度

en: Accepts a standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired yaw speed.

en: Outputs a standard value between -1 and 1 representing a stabilised yaw speed.

en: Accepts a standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired vertical speed.
local: 接受一个介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示所需的垂直速度

en: Outputs a standard value between 0 and 1 representing a stabilised upward thrust.

en: Enables the gyroscope's auto-hover circuit when receiving an on signal.

en: Interacting with [$[action_interact_left]] or [$[action_interact_right]] again will detach that hand. The handle can be used to drag vehicles around. If a vehicle is too heavy to move, you will be detached automatically when you move outside the handle's interaction range.
local: 在连接上时按[$[action_interact_left]/[$[action_interact_right]]将分离您，具体取决于您开始按了哪个键。把手可以用来拖动载具。如果载具太重而无法移动，则当您在把手的交互作用范围之外移动时，将自动分离

en: A handle that you can attach to by interacting with [$[action_interact_left]] or [$[action_interact_right]].
Sliding hatch that can be opened and closed using an on/off signal.
local: 滑动舱口，可使用开/关信号打开和关闭

en: Opens the hatch when receiving an on signal, and closes it when receiving an off signal.
local: 接收到打开信号时打开舱口，接收到关闭信号时关闭舱口

en: When enabled, the heater will warm either the compartment it is within or any players within a 10m radius, allowing them to survive cold temperatures.
local: 启用后，加热器将加热封闭空间内或半径10米范围内的所有玩家，使他们能够在寒冷的气候条件下生存

en: A small heater that will provide warmth in a radius.
local: 电暖器，可以为一定范围内的玩家提供温暖

en: Enables the heating element when receiving an on signal.
local: 在接收到接通信号时启用加热元件

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems at a rate proportional to the component's size.
local: 冷却器以与组件尺寸成比例的速率平衡两边气体的热量

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems.
local: 平衡两边气体的热量的热交换器

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems at a rate proportional to the component's size.
local: 冷却器以与组件尺寸成比例的速率平衡两边气体的热量

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems.
local: 平衡两边气体的热量的热交换器

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems at a rate proportional to the component's size.
local: 冷却器以与组件尺寸成比例的速率平衡两边气体的热量

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two air systems.
local: 平衡两边气体的热量的热交换器

en: Three standard number inputs control the rotor's swashplate, allowing you to affect the pitch, roll, and collective rotor angle. Power received from an engine affects the amount of up and down force that the rotor will generate.
local: 三个标准数字输入控制螺旋桨的旋转斜盘，允许您影响俯仰(Pitch)、侧倾和总螺旋桨角度。从发动机接收到的功率影响螺旋桨将产生的上下力的大小

en: A heavy duty rotor with thrust vectoring.
local: 带有推力矢量的重型螺旋桨

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired roll amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要滚转(Roll)的量

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要俯仰(Pitch)的量

en: Receives power generated by an engine.
local: 接收发动机产生的动力

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示总距

en: Three standard number inputs control the rotor's swashplate, allowing you to affect the pitch, roll, and collective rotor angle. Power received from an engine affects the amount of up and down force that the rotor will generate.
local: 三个标准数字输入控制螺旋桨的旋转斜盘，允许您影响俯仰(Pitch)、侧倾和总螺旋桨角度。从发动机接收到的功率影响螺旋桨将产生的上下力的大小

en: A large heavy duty rotor with thrust vectoring.
local: 带有推力矢量的大型重型螺旋桨

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired roll amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要滚转(Roll)的量

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要俯仰(Pitch)的量

en: Receives power generated by an engine.
local: 接收发动机产生的动力

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示总距

en: Two standard number inputs control the rotor's swashplate, allowing you to affect its pitch and roll. Power received from an engine affects the amount of up and down force that the rotor will generate. The output force of this rotor is decreased when underwater.
local: 两个标准数字输入控制螺旋桨的旋转斜盘，允许您影响其俯仰(Pitch)和侧倾。从发动机接收到的功率影响螺旋桨将产生的上下力的大小。在水下时，该螺旋桨的输出力减小

en: A large helicopter rotor with controllable pitch and roll.
local: 具有可控制的俯仰(Pitch)和滚转(Roll)的大型直升机旋翼

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired roll amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要滚转(Roll)的量

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示想要俯仰(Pitch)的量

en: Receives power generated by an engine.
local: 接收发动机产生的动力

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示总距

en: The reading can be read from the sensor's number output and is measured from 0 (no fog) to 1 (max fog).
local: 读数可以从传感器的数字输出中读取，测量范围为0(无雾)到1(最大雾)

en: A humidity sensor for measuring the current fog and visibility meteorological conditions.
local: 用于测量当前雾和能见度气象条件的湿度传感器

en: The level of humidity in the air, relating to the fog visibility.
local: 气体中的湿度水平，与雾的可见度有关

en: Setting the impact threshold property will tune the sensitivity for impacts. When the instant change in velocity from an impact exceeds the threshold, an on signal is produced.
local: 设置冲击阈值能够调整敏感度。 当来自撞击的瞬时速度变化超过阈值时，输出一个on信号

en: A sensor activated by a sudden change in velocity.
local: 传感器能够检测瞬间的速度变化

en: Outputs an on signal when instant change in velocity exceeds the impact threshold.
local: 当瞬间速度变化超过阈值时，输出一个on信号

en: A simple light that can be used as an indicator in logic systems.
local: 简单的指示灯,可用作逻辑系统中的指示器

en: Switches the light on when receiving an on signal.
local: 接收到接通信号时，打开灯

en: Three channels of the composite input can be used to set the red, green and blue components of the indicator's color using numbers between 0 and 1. The light can also operate in HSV mode, where the 3 inputs correspond to the hue, saturation and value (brightness) of the color between 0 and 1. The color mode and input channels can be customised by selecting this component with the select tool.
local: 组合输入的三个通道可用于使用0到1之间的数字设置指示器颜色的红色、绿色和蓝色分量。灯光也可以在HSV模式下工作，其中3个输入对应于0到1之间颜色的色调、饱和度和值(亮度)。颜色模式和输入通道可以通过使用选择工具选择此组件进行自定义

en: An advanced indicator that can be controlled using a microcontroller.
local: 可以用微控制器操作的高级指示器

en: Composite link containing the indicator's color data.
local: 包含指示器颜色数据的复合链接

en: The 4 instruments can be selected in the properties window. Each type of instrument has options for choosing the composite channels that they read from or write to. Composite signals are bridged from the input node to the output node to enable displays to be chained together. Instruments marked as '(On/Off)' require multiple on/off signals to control each of their segments individually.
local: 可以在“属性”窗口中选择这4种仪器。每种类型的仪器都有选择读写复合通道的选项。复合信号从输入节点桥接收到输出节点，以使显示链接在一起。标记为“(开/关)”的仪表需要多个开/关信号来单独控制其每个段

en: A customisable panel that can have up to 4 different instruments, controlled by a composite signal from a microcontroller.
local: 可定制的面板,可以有多达4种不同的仪器.需由微控制器的复合信号控制

en: Output signal containing data set by buttons on the display.
local: 包含由显示器上的按钮设置的数据的输出信号

en: Input signal containing data to be displayed.
local: 包含要显示的数据的输入信号

en: Enables the backlight when receiving an on signal.
local: 接收到打开信号时启用背光

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two liquid systems at a rate proportional to the component's size.
local: 冷却器以与组件尺寸成比例的速率平衡两边液体的热量

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two liquid systems.
local: 平衡两边液体的热量的热交换器

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two liquid systems at a rate proportional to the component's size.
local: 冷却器以与组件尺寸成比例的速率平衡两边液体的热量

en: A heat exchanger that averages heat between two liquid systems.
local: 平衡两边液体的热量的热交换器

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to zoom in on faraway objects.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。 按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来放大观看远处目标。 不使用时，这个装备能挂腰带上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a pair of binoculars.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个望远镜

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to arm and plant the C-4 explosive on a nearby surface.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]键将C-4炸弹放置在附近的地面上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing C-4 plastic explosive.
local: 装有C-4炸药的装备物品栏

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to detonate armed C-4 explosives.
A small equipment storage unit containing a C-4 remote detonator.
local: 小型装备架，包含一个C-4遥控起爆器

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to attach the cable to an unoccupied electrical cable anchor. Interacting with [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] on an occupied electical cable anchor will retrieve the cable if the player has inventory space to hold it.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。 按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来将电缆连接到未占用的电缆锚点。 如果有剩余空间，在已经占用的电缆锚点按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 将会把电缆收回到玩家库存。 不使用时，这个装备能够收到背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing 20m of electrical cable.
local: 大型装备架，存储共计20m长的电缆

en: When held, the red needle of the compass will point northwards. The compass also displays a bearing on the equipment hotbar UI.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。拿在手上时，红色指针会指向北方。不使用时，这个装备能挂腰带上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a compass.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个指南针

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] on an incapacitated survivor to revive them. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered large equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。对着丧失行动能力的角色按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 可以使其复苏。丧失行动能力过长时间的幸存者会无法被救活，该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的大型装备架时充电。不使用时可以放在背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a defibrillator.
local: 大型装备架，存储一个除颤器

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to sound the whistle. Nearby dogs will respond to certain whistle patterns. 1 long burst = Wait. 2 short bursts = Follow.
local: 按住[$[action_equipment_use]]吹响哨子,附近的狗狗会做出回应:1次长鸣等待,2次短鸣跟随

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a dog whistle.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个狗哨

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to spray a stream of water capable of extinguishing fires. This equipment has a limited water capacity and cannot be refilled.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。对准火焰按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 喷出一柱水来灭火。这个装备有着有限的水容量而且不能装填。不使用时可以放在背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a fire extinguisher.
local: 大型装备架，存储一个灭火器

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to heal yourself, or heal a survivor highlighted by your crosshair.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来治疗你自己, 或者准星指向的高亮幸存者。这个装备有使用次数限制，拿起其他急救包能够补充使用次数。不使用时可以挂在腰带上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a first aid kit.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个急救包

en: Hold and release [$[action_equipment_use]] to load and cast the fishing line. Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to reel in the fishing line. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] before casting to cycle the sink depth of the hook.
local: 按住[$[action_equipment_use]]并松开以抛出鱼线,按住[$[action_equipment_use]]收杆.投掷前按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 循环鱼钩的下沉深度

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a fishing rod.
local: 大型装备架，存储一套鱼竿
装备架(手持燃烧照明棒)

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to throw a red smoke flare which burns for a long time.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来扔出一个持续时间内释放红烟并发光的燃烧照明棒。这个装备有使用次数限制，拿起其他照明棒能够补充使用次数。不使用时可以挂在腰带上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing flares.
local: 小型装备架，存储一支手持燃烧照明棒

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to fire a red illumination flare that burns for a short time, and [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to reload.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来发射一个持续较短时间的发光信号弹，按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 来卸载枪中弹药，使用一盒信号枪弹药后可以让枪重新装填。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a flaregun preloaded with 1 flaregun round.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个带一发弹药的信号弹枪

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to reload an equipped flaregun.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来给在库存中没有装弹的任何信号枪装上信号弹。有着有限使用次数，拿起其他信号枪弹药能够补充使用次数。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a box flaregun ammo.
local: 小装备架，存储一盒信号枪弹药

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the flashlight on or off. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来开关手电筒。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a flashlight.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个手电筒

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle radiation detection on or off. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按[$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]]能装备/收起选中物品。按[$[action_equipment_use]]打开或关闭辐射指示器。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时，这个装备能挂腰带上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a radiation detector.
local: 小型装备架，储存一个辐射指示器

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to throw a glowstick which emits light for an extended time. The editor paint tool can be used to set the glowstick hue.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]扔出一个荧光棒，它会发光一段时间。可以使用编辑器绘制工具来设置荧光棒的色调

en: A small equipment storage unit containing glowsticks.
Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to throw a hand grenade, which will detonate after a short delay.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]投掷手榴弹，手榴弹会在短时间延迟后引爆

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a hand grenade.
local: 装有手榴弹的小型设备储存装置

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to attach the hose to an unoccupied fluid hose anchor. Interacting with [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] on an occupied fluid hose anchor will retrieve the hose if the player has inventory space to hold it. If the hose contains water, press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to toggle open the hose valve and allow the water to flow freely.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。 按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来将电缆连接到未占用的软管锚点。 如果有剩余空间，在已经占用的软管锚点按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 将会把软管收回到玩家库存。如果软管中有流体，按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 可以开关阀门允许流体自由流动。不使用时，这个装备能够收到背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing 20m of fluid hosing.
local: 大型装备架，存储20m长流体软管

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to zoom in on faraway objects. The night vision effect provides improved visibility in low light conditions, but hinders visibility in daylight. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来放大远处目标。夜视效果提供了在微光环境下更好的能见度，但在白天会受到极大影响。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a pair of night vision binoculars.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个夜视望远镜

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to recover your breath while underwater. This equipment has a limited air capacity, and will refill when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下[$[action_equipment_use]]来在水底恢复呼吸，这个装备有有限的气体容量，只有放在已供电的小型装备架时才会回复。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing an oxygen mask.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个氧气面罩

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to fire, and [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to reload. The pistol is compact enough for a belt holster, and can be accurate when recoil is carefully managed.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]开火，按[$[action_equipment_secondary]]重新装填。这种手枪足够紧凑，可以配备一个枪套，并且在小心地控制后坐力时可以精确射击

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a pistol.
local: 装有手枪的小型设备储存装置

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to reload an equipped pistol.
A small equipment storage unit containing a pistol ammo magazine.
local: 装有手弹匣库的小型装备储存装置

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] transmit voice audio. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to cycle between frequencies 0~8, or turn the radio off. When a frequncy is selected, the radio will transmit and receive voice audio on that frequency only. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit. (Max Effective Range : 500m)
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来发送语音，按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 来在频道0~8之间切换或关掉无线电。当选中一个特定频率后，无线电只会在该频率上收发音频信号。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时可以挂在腰上(最大距离500m)

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a handheld radio.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个手持无线电
装备架(无线电信号定位器)

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the locator on or off. When active, the locator produces audible beeps that increase in frequency as the player nears an active transponder. The handheld locator has a shorter detection range than the vehicle mounted locator, but can narrow down the target location to a smaller area. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered large equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下[$[action_equipment_use]]来开关定位器。当打开时，定位器会持续发出滴滴声，并且越接近信号源滴滴声频率越高。手持无线电定位器的有效范围比载具定位器小，但能够在小范围内更加精确定位。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的大型装备架时充电。不使用时可以放在背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a handheld transponder locator.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个手持无线电信号定位器

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the remote control on or off. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to cycle between frequencies 0~8. When active, the remote control uses the basic vehicle pilot seat input bindings and transmits them as composite radio data on the selected frequency. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit. (Max Effective Range : 500m)
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来切换远程控制开关，按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 来循环0~8的频率。当开启时，远程控制将玩家操作输出为混合信号(参照基础载具控制)发送到指定频率。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时可以挂在腰上(最大距离500m)

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a remote control unit.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个远程控制单元

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to fire, and [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to reload. The rifle fires accurate and powerful shots for long-range engagements.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]开火，按[$[action_equipment_secondary]]重新装填。这种步枪能准确而有力地进行远程射击

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a rifle.
local: 装有步枪的大型装备架

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to reload an equipped rifle.
A small equipment storage unit containing a rifle ammo magazine.
local: 小型装备架，包含一个步枪弹匣

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to attach the rope to any rope anchor. Interacting with [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] on an occupied rope anchor will retrieve the rope if the player has inventory space to hold it.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。 按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来将绳索连接到未占用的绳索锚点。 如果有剩余空间，在已经占用的绳索锚点按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 将会把绳索收回到玩家库存。 不使用时，这个装备能够收到背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing 20m of rope.
local: 大型装备架，存储20m长绳索

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to fire, and [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to reload. The SMG has a high rate of fire and magazine capacity.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]开火，按[$[action_equipment_secondary]]重新装填。冲锋枪的火力和弹仓容量都很高

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a submachine gun.
local: 装有冲锋枪的大型装备架

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to reload an equipped submachine gun.
A small equipment storage unit containing a submachine gun ammo magazine.
local: 包含冲锋枪弹匣的小型装备架

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to fire, and [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to reload. The speargun can be fired underwater and spears travel through the water more effectively than bullets.
local: 按[$[action_equipment_use]]开火，按[$[action_equipment_secondary]]重新装填。鱼叉枪可以在水下发射，较重的长矛在水中比子弹更有效

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a speargun.
local: 大型装备架，内有一把鱼叉枪

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to reload an equipped speargun.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来给在库存中没有装弹的鱼叉枪装上弹药。有着有限使用次数，拿起其他鱼叉枪弹药能够补充使用次数。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a box of speargun ammo.
local: 小型装备架，存储一盒鱼叉枪弹药

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the strobe light on or off. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to toggle MOB (man overboard) mode, which will automatically turn the strobe light on if the player is submerged in water. The strobe light will continue to function when unequipped or discarded. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来开关频闪灯。按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 开关MOB(落水)模式，MOB模式下会在玩家落入水中时自动打开频闪。频闪灯在不被装备时依然会继续作用。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时会被挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a strobe light.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个频闪灯

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the strobe light on or off. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to toggle MOB (man overboard) mode, which will automatically turn the strobe light on if the player is submerged in water. The strobe light will continue to function when unequipped or discarded. The infrared strobe light flashes are only visible to infrared cameras. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来开关频闪灯。按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 开关MOB(落水)模式，MOB模式下会在玩家落入水中时自动打开频闪。频闪灯在不被装备时依然会继续作用。红外频闪灯只能被红外模式下的摄像头观察到。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时可以挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing an infrared strobe light.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个红外频闪灯

en: Press [$[action_equipment_use]] to toggle the transponder on or off. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to toggle MOB (man overboard) mode, which will automatically turn the transponder on if the player is submerged in water. The transponder will continue to function when unequipped or discarded. Requires electric charge to function, and will recharge when placed into a powered small equipment storage unit.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按下 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来开关应急信标。按下 [$[action_equipment_secondary]] 开关MOB(落水)模式，MOB模式下会在玩家落入水中时自动启动应急信标。该信标在不被装备时依然会继续作用。该设备需要充电才能发挥作用，放入已供电的小型装备架时充电。不使用时会被挂在腰上

en: A small equipment storage unit containing a handheld transponder.
local: 小型装备架，存储一个手持应急信标

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to repair damaged vehicle components highlighted by the players crosshair. The underwater welding torch holds less fuel than the standard welding torch, but can be operated while submerged in water. This equipment has a limited fuel capacity and cannot be refilled.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来维修准星指向的载具部件。水下火旱枪比标准火旱枪携带更少的燃料，但是能够在水下工作。这个装备燃料有限而且不能补充。不使用时可以放在背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing an underwater welding torch.
local: 大型装备架，存储一个水下火旱枪 [译注:这游戏不支持han字...]

en: Hold [$[action_equipment_use]] to repair damaged vehicle components highlighted by the players crosshair. This equipment has a limited fuel capacity and cannot be refilled.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。按住 [$[action_equipment_use]] 来维修准星指向的载具部件。这个装备燃料有限而且不能补充。不使用时可以放在背后

en: A large equipment storage unit containing a welding torch.
local: 大型装备架，存储一个火旱枪 [译注:这游戏不支持han字...]

en: Only large handheld equipment can be stored in this unit. When connected to an electric power source, any rechargable equipment stored in the unit will drain a small amount of electricity until recharged to 100% capacity.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。只有大型手持装备能够放在这个架子中。当连接到电源时，其内的装备可以得到充电

en: An empty large equipment storage unit.

Interacting with [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] will equip/store the selected outfit. Only specialist outfits can be stored in this unit. When connected to an electric power source, any rechargable outfits stored in the unit will drain a small amount of electricity until recharged to 100% capacity.
local: 如果你穿的是专业服装，按$[action_interact_left]/[$[action_interact_right]]将其储存在本单元中。当连接上电源时，会自动对其中装备进行充电

en: When equipped, it will increase your temperature enough to survive in colder weather conditions. Its thermal effectiveness is reduced when wet.
local: 按 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]]将装备/储存装备。装备后，它会使你的体温升高，足以在更冷的天气条件下生存。湿的时候它的热效率会降低

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist thermal clothing for surviving Arctic temperatures.
local: 装有保暖服的装备架，用于抵御极地的严寒

en: When equipped, it will allow deep sea diving to a depth of 230m, and provides air for 10 minutes. The air tank can be refilled by storing the gear in an outfit inventory unit with an attached air input or via space seat.
local: 装备潜水服后,最大潜深可达到230米,最大续航时间10分钟.将潜水服放入带有空气输入的装备架,或使用太空座椅可为潜水服充气

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist diving equipment.
local: 包含专业潜水设备的装备架

en: When equipped, it will absorb 95% of damage dealt by fires.
local: 按 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]]将装备/储存装备。装备后，它将吸收95%的火灾伤害

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist firefighting gear.
local: 包含专业消防装备的装备架

en: When equipped, it will absorb 95% of incoming radiation.
local: 按 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]]将装备/储存装备。装备后，将吸收95%的辐射伤害

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist hazmat gear.
local: 包含一套专业化学防护服的装备架

en: When selected, press [$[action_equipment_use]] while falling to deploy the parachute. It will then open when you are falling fast enough. Press [$[action_equipment_secondary]] to close the parachute. This parachute is single-use once equipped but can be refolded by storing it in an outfit inventory unit.
local: 按 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]]将装备/储存装备。装备后，在降落时按 [$[action_use_seat]] 将展开降落伞。当你下降得够快的时候它就会打开。再次按 [$[action_use_seat]] 将关闭它。这种降落伞一经装备就可以一次性使用，但可以通过储存在装备架单元中重新折叠

en: An outfit inventory unit containing a single-use parachute.
local: 装有一次性降落伞的装备架

en: When equipped, it will allow diving to a depth of 40m, and provides air for 2 minutes. The air tank can be refilled by storing the gear in an outfit inventory unit with an attached air input or via space seat.
local: 装备潜水服后,最大潜深可达到40米,最大续航时间2分钟.将潜水服放入带有空气输入的装备架,或使用太空座椅可为潜水服充气

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist scuba gear.
local: 包含一套专业的潜水装备的装备架

en: When equipped, it will protect against low temperatures, low pressures and provide oxygen.
local: 防止低温低压并提供氧气的套装

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist Space Exploration gear required for surviving in space. The air tank can be refilled by storing the gear in an outfit inventory unit with an attached air input or via space seat.
local: 包含一套为太空探索准备的航天服.将航天服放入带有空气输入的装备架,或使用太空座椅可为航天服充气

en: When equipped, it will protect against low temperatures, low pressures and provide oxygen.
local: 防止低温低压并提供氧气的套装

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist Space Exploration gear required for surviving in space. The air tank can be refilled by storing the gear in an outfit inventory unit with an attached air input or via space seat.
local: 包含一套为太空探索准备的探索型航天服.将航天服放入带有空气输入的装备架,或使用太空座椅可为航天服充气

en: When equipped, damage from projectiles to the body and head is greatly reduced.  Wearing the outfit significantly limits movement speed.
local: 当装备时，大幅降低身体与头部所受到的投射物伤害，同时大幅降低移动速度

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist millitary clothing for projectile protection.
local: 包含一套军用防弹背心的装备架

en: When equipped, damage from projectiles to the body is reduced slightly.
local: 当装备时，略微降低身体所受到的投射物伤害

local: 包含一套军用防弹背心的装备架

local: 当装备时，极大降低身体与头部所受到的投射物与爆炸物伤害，同时也极大降低移动速度

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist millitary clothing for projectile protection.
local: 包含一套战术胸挂的装备架

en: When equipped, damage from projectiles to the body is reduced significantly and damage to the head is greatly reduced.  Wearing the outfit significantly limits movement speed.
local: 当装备时，极大降低身体、大幅降低头部所受到的投射物伤害，同时极大降低移动速度

en: An outfit inventory unit containing specialist millitary clothing for projectile protection.
local: 包含一套战术插板胸挂的装备架

en: Only small handheld equipment can be stored in this unit. When connected to an electric power source, any rechargable equipment stored in the unit will drain a small amount of electricity until recharged to 100% capacity.
local: 按下 [$[action_interact_left]]/[$[action_interact_right]] 能装备/收起选中物品。只有小型手持装备能够放在这个架子中。当连接到电源时，其内的装备可以得到充电

local: 喷气引擎的排气装置之一,可以燃烧额外的燃料以增加输出

local: 您可以按[$[action_use_seat]]连接收到梯子，然后按[$[action_use_seat]]或[$[action_jump]]再次分离。到达顶部时，您将自动从梯子上分离

local: 单梯横档。多个横档可以相互叠放，形成一个任意长度的梯子

local: 非常适合安装在直升机上，使其能够在海上降落

en: Power received from an engine affects the forward and backward force generated. This propeller will only operate underwater.

en: Receives power generated by an engine.
local: 接收发动机产生的动力

en: Standard value between -1 and 1 representing the desired pitch amount.
local: 介于-1和1之间的标准值，表示俯仰(Pitch)角

以米为单位测量的距离

en: The closest point to the center of the sensor's field of view will be reported. It outputs a value of -1 to 1 on composite number channel 1 for the x position, and a value of -1 to 1 on composite number channel 2 for the y position. Composite on/off channel 1 is set to on when a point is visible. The -1 to 1 values map to an fov of -cos(0.5) to cos(0.5) in both the x and y directions.
local: 在混合通道输出距离视场中心最近的激光点(相同激光编码).number通道1:x位置(-1到1).number通道2:y位置(-1到1).boolean通道1:发现激光点.-1到1的值在x和y方向上都映射为-cos(0.5)到cos(0.5)的视场

en: A sensor that outputs a relative x and y position of a laser point that it can see within its field of view.
local: 输出在其视场内探测到的激光点的相对x和y位置的传感器

en: On/Off channel 1: is laser detected. Number channel 1, 2: X, Y position within the sensors 120 degree field of view.

en: You can build the track using the Linear Track Extension component. This base component provides 3 blocks that can be built on. A pair of on/off signals allow you to control the up and down motion of the slider, and a numerical output lets you measure the slider's offset from its starting position. Multiple slider bases can run along the same track. The up/down speed can be configured by selecting this component with the select tool.
local: 可以使用“线性轨迹扩展”组件构建轨迹。这个基本组件提供了3个可以构建的块。一对开/关信号允许您控制滑块的上下运动，一个数字输出允许您测量滑块从其起始位置的偏移。多个滑块底座可以沿同一轨迹运行。可通过使用选择工具选择该部件来配置上升/下降速度

en: It can connect drill rods together to lengthen them, or separate drill rods to shorten them.
local: 可以将钻杆连接在一起以延长其长度,或将钻杆分开以缩短其长度

en: A clamp for moving drill rods into place.
local: 用于将钻杆移至适当位置的夹具

en: Attach a drill rod to the clamp.
Returns true when a drill rod is attached.
Moves an attached drill rod up or down the clamp.
local: 将夹持的钻杆向上或向下移动

en: Connects or disconnects a pair of drill rods when the ends are aligned at the connection point.
local: 当两根钻杆对准连接点时,将一对钻杆连接或断开

en: Returns true when the connection point aligns over the end of a pair of drill rods.
local: 当一对钻杆对准连接点时,返回true

en: Torque provided by an external motor rotates the table, which can rotate a drill rod placed through the center of the table.
local: 由外部供能的旋转台,可以使转台中央的钻杆旋转

en: A rotary table for drilling in an oil rig.
Attach a drill rod to the table. This will transfer any rotation of the table to the attached drill rod.
local: 控制钻台是否夹持钻杆以带动钻杆旋转

en: Torque connection to power the rotation of the table.
local: 为钻台提供动力的扭矩入口

en: The rotations per second of the table.
A clamp for moving drill rods into place.
local: 用来抓取并移动钻杆的夹具

en: Attach a drill rod to the clamp.
Returns true when a drill rod is attached.
Slides an attached drill rod up or down the clamp.
local: 将夹持的钻杆向上或向下移动

en: A clamp for moving drill rods into place.
local: 用来抓取并移动钻杆的夹具

en: Attach a drill rod to the clamp.
Returns true when a drill rod is attached.
Contains a single drill rod when spawned.
A storage rack for drill rods.
Returns true when a drill rod is stored in the component.
local: 当钻杆被存储在组件中时返回true

en: The swivel connects to the end of a drill rod, and has fluid ports for drilling slurry and crude oil. Pumping a supply of drilling slurry through a drill rod is required for effective drilling.
local: 泥浆喷嘴接到钻杆的末端,并有泥浆和原油的出入口.为了高效钻探,需要将泥浆泵入钻杆

en: A swivel for transferring fluids through a drill rod.
local: 用于通过钻杆输送流体的设备

en: Attach a drill rod to the swivel.
Returns true when a drill rod is attached.
Fluid port to transfer drilling slurry through an attached rod linked to a well.
local: 将泥浆泵入钻杆的入口

en: Fluid port to transfer drilling slurry from an attached rod linked to a well.
local: 钻井串联时用到的泥浆出口

en: Pulling the piston of the pumpjack with enough force will lift the piston, pulling fluid through the pump. A mechanical force capable of repeatedly cycling the piston is required to pump fluid effectively.
local: 用足够的力量拉动泵架的活塞,就会抬起活塞，以拉动流体通过液泵.为了有效地泵送流体,需要一个能够反复循环活塞的机械力

en: A pumpjack for extracting crude oil from a drilled oil well.
local: 用于从钻好的油井中抽取原油的抽油机

en: Once anchored to the terrain, a drill rod can be inserted into a well head to begin drilling a well. In order to drill effectively a drill rod should be driven by a rotary table and forced downward toward the terrain. A continuous supply of drilling slurry must be provided through the drill rod via a swivel, and the saturated drilling slurry extracted from the well head fluid port.
local: 一旦锚定在地形上,就可以将钻杆插入井口,开始钻井.为了有效地进行钻探,应通过钻机旋转台驱动钻杆,并使其向地面下移.必须通过钻机旋转台向钻杆持续供应钻井泥浆,并从井口流体出口抽取饱和泥浆

en: A well head for oil drilling.

Extend / retract piles to anchor the well head to the terrain, allowing for a new well to be drilled. The well head must be close to the terrain (~1m) and upright (+-30 degrees) to be anchored. Unanchoring the well will reset any drilling progress made.
local: 延长/缩短地桩以将井口锚定在地形上.井口必须靠近地形(约1米)并直立(+-30度)才能被锚定.解除井的锚定将重置钻探的进展

en: Returns true when the well head is anchored to the terrain.
local: 当井口被锚定在地形上时返回true

en: Returns the depth of an attached drill rod in meters.
local: 以米为单位的钻杆深度

en: Returns the depth of the drilled well in meters.

The parachute will deploy when receiving an on signal, and will close when not. Once deployed, it will open at a speed of 20m/s and stall when it drops below 5m/s. Once opened, the single use will be consumed and it must be returned to a workbench to be refolded. The size of the parachute can be customised by selecting this component with the select tool.
local: 降落伞将在收到打开信号时展开，否则将关闭。一旦展开，它将在20m/s的速度打开，当速度降至5m/s以下时停止。一旦打开，一次性使用将被消耗，必须返回工作台重新折叠。通过使用选择工具选择该组件，可以定制降落伞的尺寸

en: A single-use parachute that can be deployed to reduce a vehicle's velocity.
local: 一次性的降落伞，可以用来降低载具的速度

en: Deploy the parachute. The parachute will close when it stalls or stops receiving an on signal.
local: 展开降落伞。当降落伞失速或停止接收到打开信号时，降落伞将关闭

en: You can get in and out of the seat by interacting with it using [$[action_use_seat]]. You can place a rescued survivor in any seat by using [$[action_use_seat]] while carrying them.
local: 通过使用[$[action_use_seat]]与座椅交互，您可以进出座椅。您可以在携带获救幸存者时使用[$[action_use_seat]]将其放置在任何座椅上

en: Outputs an on signal if this seat is occupied by a character.
local: 如果该座位被角色占用，则输出接通信号

en: Floods an enclosed volume with massless physics, allowing for physics shape optimisation without comprimising vehicle integrity.
local: 用零重量的方块填满密闭空间(不能用于有可动部件的房间)

en: A device that floods an enclosed volume with physics for optimisation.
local: 可以在封闭的空间中注入用零重量的方块以进行优化的装置

en: Outputs physics information to a composite logic node. Requires Electric for GPS position functionality. This component is directed along its local Y axis.
local: 将检测到的物理信息以混合信号发送出。需要连接电力以使用GPS功能。方块的方向以他自身的Y轴（绿色箭头朝向）朝向为准。

en: Sensor component that outputs various physics measurements such as position and velocity.
local: 检测例如位置以及速度等不同物理信息的传感器

en: Outputs [1] x position, [2] y position, [3] z position, [4] euler rotation x, [5] euler rotation y, [6] euler rotation z, [7] linear velocity x, [8] linear velocity y, [9] linear velocity z, [10] angular velocity x, [11] angular velocity y, [12] angular velocity z, [13] absolute linear velocity, [14] absolute angular velocity, [15] local z tilt, [16] local x tilt and [17] compass heading (-0.5 to 0.5) to the respective composite channels.
local:
输出
1. x坐标
2. y坐标
3. z坐标
4. x轴旋转量
5. y轴旋转量
6. z轴旋转量
7. x轴速度
8. y轴速度
9. z轴速度
10. x轴角速度
11. y轴角速度
12. z轴角速度
13. 绝对速度
14. 绝对角速度
(箭头红色x轴、绿色y轴、蓝色z轴)
15.Z轴倾斜
16.X轴倾斜
17.方向(-0.5~0.5)

en: If the sensor is facing into a sealed room, only players inside that room will be detected. Likewise, players inside sealed rooms will not be detected if the sensor is placed on the outside. The size of the area and types of players to detect can be changed by selecting this component with the select tool.
local: 如果传感器正对着一个密封的房间，则只会检测到房间内的玩家。同样，如果传感器放在外面，密封房间内的玩家也不会被检测到。通过使用选择工具选择此组件，可以更改要检测的区域大小和玩家类型

en: A sensor that outputs the number of players detected within an area.
local: 输出在一个区域内检测到的玩家数量的传感器

en: The number of players detected by the sensor.
local: 传感器检测到的玩家数量

en: Outputs an on signal if any players are detected.
local: 如果检测到任何玩家，则输出开启信号

en: Setting the resistance property will tune the amount of contact required to depress the sensor. When depressed, an on signal will be produced.
local: 设置阻值将调整按下传感器所需的接触量。按下时，将产生接通信号

en: A sensor activated by contact pressure.
local: 由接触压力激活的传感器

en: Outputs an on signal when the contact sensor is depressed.
local: 按下压力传感器时，输出接通信号

local: 接收发动机产生的动力

local: 接收发动机产生的动力

local: 输入-1~1之间的数字以调桨距

local: 该传感器将输出其范围和视野内的检测对象的距离和角度。(最大距离:5000)(最大视场:0.125)

en: A short range Radar that returns information about a detected object within its view.
local: 短程雷达，返回其视野内探测到的物体的信息

en: The sensor's yaw field of view in turns from 0.01 to 0.125.
local: 传感器的偏航视野从0.01到0.125依次变化

en: The sensor's yaw direction in turns from -0.5 to 0.5.
local: 传感器的偏航方向从-0.5到0.5

en: The distance to the target in meters.
The strength of the returned signal.
The pitch angle between the sensor and the target in turns.
local: 传感器和目标之间的俯仰角

en: Returns if an object has been detected.
local: 如果检测到对象，则返回

en: A radar that returns information about a detected object within its view.
local: 返回其视野内探测到的物体的信息

en: Outputs data for up to 8 targets. On/Off 1-8 : Target 1 Found, Target 2 Found, etc... local: 当前雷达从前方开始自转

local: 远程雷达，返回视野内探测到的物体的信息

en: A small solid rocket fuel segment.

en: A small solid rocket fuel segment with in-built controllable fins.

en: Composite data for the control surfaces.

This sensor outputs the relative angle to detected objects within its range using underwater sound waves. The sensor will passively detect certain noisy components such as propellers or engines but can also send out a loud ping to detect quiet underwater bodies. While the ping input is held passive signals will be supressed. After activating a ping additional detected signals will appear momentarily in the data channel as the signal returns to the sonar. Activating another ping will override the previous ping and no further data will be returned from the old signal.
local: 声纳可在水下利用声波探测其探测范围内检测到的物体的相对角度。被动模式可监听测某些嘈杂的部件,如螺旋桨或发动机。也可主动发出一个响亮的Ping来检测安静的水下物体。主动Ping时,无法检测到被动信号。激活Ping后,当信号返回到声纳时,额外的检测信号将暂时出现在数据通道中。激活新的Ping将覆盖前一个Ping,旧信号将不再返回数据

en: A sonar that returns information about a detected objects within 60km.
local: 该声纳最大可探测60km内的物体

en: Send a ping and listen for return sounds.
local: 进行一次Ping的发送并监听

en: Outputs data for up to 16 targets. On/Off 1-16 : Target 1 Found, Target 2 Found, Etc... Values 1-32: Target 1 Pivot, Target 1 Pitch, Target 2 Pivot, Target 2 Pitch, Etc...

en: Steam pressurized through the outer coupling extends the piston and steam pressurized through the inner coupling retracts the piston. Alternating pressure to the couplings based on the piston position will allow the crankpin to rotate continuously.
local: 通过外侧联轴器加压的蒸汽使活塞伸出,通过内侧联轴器加压的蒸汽使活塞缩回.根据活塞的位置来调整联轴器的压力,可以使曲轴连续旋转.(P.S:就像真正的蒸汽机一样,为了避免失速,最好有一个飞轮或多个不相干的活塞.这是因为曲轴上的扭矩作用在冲程的末端有低效率区,就像真正的活塞一样.彼此相邻的活塞被锁定在一起,但可以用玩家定义的曲柄周期偏移来生成.这允许对发动机的建造方式进行大量的控制.)

en: A steam powered piston that converts steam pressure into torque.
local: 以蒸汽为动力的活塞，将蒸汽压力转换为扭矩

This can be used to transport water between Two bodies. Two on/off signals are used to control whether the hose is moving up (towards the base) or down (away from the base). A number output allows you to measure the hose's current length if necessary. The maximum length of the hose is 16 metres (64 blocks). The speed of the hose mechanism can be configured by selecting this component with the select tool.
